member.name: T:B4.FoundationLibrary.DataProtector
member.summary:
Applications often need to store sensitive data like connection strings and user credentials. This type of data should never be stored as plain text. The Data Protection API (part of the CryptoAPI) has Encrypt and Decrypt to store encrypted data in the User or Machine store.
One thing to note: The strings will still be on the managed heap as plain text during execution of these functions.
